summary: An ordinance amending sections 2 and 4, Ordinance No. 15919, entitled: "An ordinance granting to William R. Crawford, his successors and assigns, a franchise to construct, maintain and operate a system of street railways in the City of Seattle" passed by the City Council April 22, 1907, and became an ordinance pursuant to section 16 of Article 4 of the City Charter, May 6, 1907, accepted May 20, 1907.
